casebody.data:
Cornelia Ernst, as Administratrix, &c., Plaintiff, and Eusebia F. Conant, Impleaded, Appellant, v. Wilhelmina Catherine Schaeffer, Impleaded, &c., Respondent. Decided June 23, 1887. Appeal by Eusebia F. Con-ant from judgment dismissing complaint on the merits, Avith costs. W. S. Macfarlane, for appellant. H. J. Schenck, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Freedman, J.

Opinion Per Curiam.

Judgment affirmed, Avith costs against appellant.
